ODD OR EVEN

AIM:
Write a PL/SQL query to find the number whether it is odd or even.

ALGORITHM:
Step1: Start
Step2: Declare a variable A
Step3: Read variable A
Step4: IF value of 2 = 0
Step5: Display even
Step6: Else display odd
Step7: End


CODE

DECLARE
A NUMBER(10);

BEGIN
A:=&A;
IF MOD(A,2)=0 THEN
DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('EVEN');
ELSE
DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('ODD');
END IF;

END;
/
